      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MONEY PIT (1) was below best last time when sixth at The Gardens but three back was a Grade 5 winner in the quickest time on the card at The Gardens. Safe beginner and drawn well on the inside. Better than latest and can atone here. HERA ROLEX (3) could manage only sixth at Wentworth Park last time but impressed when posting an excellent 29.23 over 515m at this track the start prior. Smart winner two back and looks a key chance on that form. MY FAIRY BREAD (2) was in the minors two back (29.84) at this track but ran below best last time at Wentworth Park, finishing 7th. Goes very well here at the trip finding the frame in each of three starts. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Worth following up. BOUND'S MISSILE (6) will be hard to beat with a drop in distance.",
